full_text: I know that you learn from failures, but it still terrifies me that no matter what I do, I can‚Äôt be perfect. I can never accept that. My BF tells me constantly that it‚Äôll drive me nuts if I keep thinking about it and constantly try to change things like my character designs.

full_text: Lately, I‚Äôve been taking steps back to reflect on my self and hold myself accountable if I did something wrong. Even if I do regret it and apologize, I still feel awful and I have it on my mind for days. Even if it‚Äôs resolved civilly, I still feel bad. I‚Äôm scared to fail.

full_text: So much has happened this year. My grandmother passed away to COVID and so did my boyfriend‚Äôs grandmother. It‚Äôs been hard for the both of us, but I‚Äôm thankful to have him in my life. He‚Äôs always been there for me, and he was the big reason why I managed to start my comic.
